dering how reflection in the native image requires registration for queried members, though some might be automatic if they're constants because their type and signature are fixed. TypeUtil's type parameter is dynamic at runtime, but the test passes a Class constant. I wonder if native analysis optimizes across libraries. If the metadata is generated by an agent filtering for org.mortbay, does that mean only accesses to it are recorded? I think tests should help generate the metadata for the BigInteger constructor.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_J2iirtCUUxhYN19P6h9gj312|fc_0215cb58b73f4e5f0169f6228084688191acacb006aa542a97", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata tests/src/org.mortbay.jetty/jetty-util/6.1.26/src/test/resources -maxdepth 10 -type f | grep -E 'mortbay|jetty-util|reachability' | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 975, "output": 1318, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17141, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777738350306, "responseId": "resp_0215cb58b73f4e5f0169f6226ea76481918636017a66e138f1"}}
