[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing Native Image Metadata**\n\nI’m thinking that Native Image needs metadata for the test class constructor. Since the dynamic access target might be a user class, the agent filter could exclude test classes. Metadata is generated in native images, and tests should run there too. If TypeUtil.valueOf(ConstructorBackedValue.class, \"alpha\") uses reflection to access the constructor, things might fail unless the test class is included in the metadata. I wonder if reachability metadata for tests is possible? I might check using a JDK class with a String constructor.\n\n**Examining Reflection in Native Image**\n\nI’m pondering how reflection in the native image requires registration for queried members, though some might be automatic if they're constants because their type and signature are fixed. TypeUtil's type parameter is dynamic at runtime, but the test passes a Class constant. I wonder if native analysis optimizes across libraries. If the metadata is generated by an agent filtering for org.mortbay, does that mean only accesses to it are recorded? I think tests should help generate the metadata for the BigInteger constructor.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0215cb58b73f4e5f0169f6226f44188191977ac3ecb3e3ce1b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9iKAX6jCdryw1H0ySbMZNHQ57mQQB43nGsq1skaACO8mZHKK9mG4cGyPwgn6G6vaAQrekv0gFYriorE8iFT8uZR5EQh7-B4ZSmuye30fe_ubs46DljUIbzSSWmNqBhCekJ2xb_aUeABiOe4tobECfHzzlBAi3gzkIp64Y-4pmaljzK3M93IZl_QHPMhYDmaQeZ_sm7oBtpBEl33KRrPbwH8ul3q3fEmwqMlH53NKu1njx9hlJcEZBuKvWnRomWJEWlvsIPyf8zU5aN7myXKTiu9mf6uIKTjh-lEU9v0WCE69OyoCczuH5VjgSr1_fQs-79DFTQ7fBcmmpfggxneVxKNZBQoguNQ8-oGJoQYSCmeLrXar-Go9nH4c0KQjswdXHfT9l_J-fSYU7YWJbmAW6QbvpBz9sAtkP4kY0GGq2gWINdGjh1CVIv0kF1ASHi6ThSJ1xXra8_GIkraparlxJO14vyD3XkUrb0Y7D-qRvViucrDFFsgReYiu8eqhhvgJqiR1FKo99JRIiET2RpPb5jwvsNLJ-1FvDmi-fSz9cfJgoQMRzYrfzdevaHKJovy9hzs_B6-MqGJAAKFT9lg